# Asset Conventions

## Organization

All production assets live in `public/images/` organized by category:

| Folder           | Contents                                  |
|------------------|-------------------------------------------|
| `brand/`         | Reloadux logo, tkxel logo                 |
| `logos/`         | Client logo SVGs                          |
| `blog/`          | Blog post cover images                    |
| `testimonials/`  | Avatar photos, company logos              |
| `portfolio/`     | Portfolio/case study slide images & videos |
| `cta/`           | CTA section company images                |
| `covers/`        | Hero and section background images        |
| `icons/`         | Shared icons (arrows, badges, decorative) |

## Naming Conventions

- **All files**: kebab-case, descriptive names (e.g., `ai-first-redesign.webp`, not `img1.webp`)
- **Client logos**: `{company}-{variant}.svg` (e.g., `barclays-2.svg`)
- **Blog images**: `{slug}.webp`
- **Testimonial avatars**: `{first-name}.webp`
- **Company logos**: `{company}-logo.webp`
- **Portfolio slides**: `{project}-slide.webp`

## Format Rules

| Format | Use for                                    |
|--------|--------------------------------------------|
| SVG    | Logos, icons, all vector graphics           |
| WebP   | Photographs, cover images, raster graphics |
| PNG    | Only when WebP is unavailable              |
| JPEG   | Never use — convert to WebP                |

## Usage in Code

- Always use `next/image` `<Image>` component for raster images (WebP, PNG)
- Use native `<img>` only for SVGs that need to fill their container
- Reference paths from `public/`: `src="/images/logos/barclays-2.svg"`
- Always provide `width` and `height` props to `<Image>` for layout stability
- Use `priority` prop on above-the-fold hero images
